g machines that take up little space from  m² this form of distribution is often referred to by its english equivalent as vending shopzones areas of shopin gas stations truck stops or other places frequented by the public where goods are offered to the consumer these zones are usually large at  square feet food service business such as food service specialist in retail establishments with less than  m² of retail space this category also includes the wellknown mom and pop shop and the kiosk food selfservice business such as food selfservice specialist retail business with less than  m² of retail space this includes the us britain and japan is very successful convenience store from which the future is also expected to play a greater role in germany  site for liesel meijer hendrik g sbfood market food business with  sqm to  sqm retail space that includes a limited range of fresh produce as well as smaller nonfood ranges in selfservice supermarket a selfservice grocery store with a sales area of  and  square feet besides fresh produce it offers extensive nonfood ranges selfservice stores and supermarkets carry  articles consumer market on a founding selfservice retail store with retail space of  m² and  m the predominant food supply and one common share of over  of nonfood items place of commerce stationary trade in stores hawking on markets through doorstep selling mail order including ecommerce teleshopping number of sites active single multiplant companies affiliated companies location and neighborhood  raft of other retail formats galleries arcades retail centers multifunction centers  site for liesel meijer hendrik g special case of direct sales direct selling is a special form of goods distribution to consumers and  or final users without counting the retail sector doing some trading functions and the distribution of goods are taken over by the manufacturer itself within the direct sales there are a variety of guises such as ecommerce doorstep sales factory outlet