ale commercial marketing for several years it is observed that the end user to turn aggressive pricing discount stores and other retail businesses increasingly prefer such which through entertainment experiences and special ambience of additional benefit for example urban entertainment centers this trend is described as a polarization of the retail trade or as a loss of center walmart according to american agricultural products in the average lay on their way from field to retail back to  km   site for liesel meijer hendrik g these and other trends may have problematic consequences in urban planning employment policy and spatial planning aspects a the relocation of largescale retail enterprises from the growing and planned centers in outlying areas which cause as retail locations usually lower operational costs threatened with obliteration of the centers b due to the ever progressive market penetration of individual branches by chain stores and retail chains with its largely uniform architectural design the shopping streets in the center and lose their individuality always interchangeable c the employment in retail trade is declining sharply for years as is required in largescale operation types less staff per m² of retail space this trend particularly affects women who are employed in retail trade compared with other industries on average the gender discrimination against women in the retail allotted an extra dimension control in germany since the s and increasingly since the s in germany there are efforts in the field of building law and planning law to prevent the urban and regional planning problematic effects or attenuate the main features of the regulations and recommendations have outlined the most federal countries in socalled retail decrees many communities and regions are looking at the foundation of the building regulations and planning laws therefore in socalled retail concepts determine what criteria which retail operations should be planned and located