 expo jun  venue gaylord national harbor hotel washington united states meijer crosses bridge into michigans upper peninsula may   meijer opened new supercenters in escanaba and sault ste the squarefoot stores bring shoppers a onestop shopping experience that features low prices on highquality merchandise grocery delivered daily and a fullservice pharmacy that makes family health care a priority the grocery options that meijer offers to shoppers include more than  varieties of farmfresh produce and a fullservice meat department that features fresh seafood certified angus beef and custom cuts of meat the stores also offer a large selection of general merchandise including womens apparel home goods school supplies and sports and camping gear meijer opens two new supercenters in indiana may   meijer opened new squarefoot supercenters in mccordsville and franklin ind bringing residents a new onestop shopping option that features low prices on groceries highquality merchandise and a fullservice pharmacy that makes family health care a priority the new stores will also offer the shipthome delivery service which recently launched across indianapolis and continues to gain popularity with customers looking for another convenient way to shop with  stores throughout indiana the new locations are built to leadership in energy and environmental design leed standards and are the latest in a  million investment this year that includes the construction of seven new meijer supercenters and remodel projects for  additional stores in indiana illinois michigan ohio and kentucky the grand rapids michbased familyowned retailer is also featuring the option for its new home delivery service for customers of its new stores the stores also demonstrated their commitment to the community by making donations to local organizations the mccordsville store director tim snyder presented  to the mt vernon community school corporation to help establish collegechoice   savings accounts for all mt vern